item.description:
@cocoa wrote:

kk then search public boolean nonwild and then use those codes to make a nonwild place… you should be able to figure out what the code means on your own as I did also but if you don’t then here is a hint
“AbsX> ####(smallest x coordinate)”
“AbsX< ####(largest x coordinate)”
“AbsY> ####(smallest y coordinate)”
“AbsY< ####(largest y coordinate)”
